This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new method for Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) search using a differential architecture search strategy and Global Latent Optimization (GLO) procedure. It also mentions achieving state-of-the-art results in various tasks such as classification and semantic segmentation, which are common applications of machine learning. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as GANs are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image generation and image-to-image translation. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as GANs are a popular topic in the field of AI and the paper proposes a new method for optimizing GANs. 

It could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as GANs are a type of neural network and the paper proposes a new method for optimizing the generator architecture. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.GR (Graphics) as GANs are commonly used in graphics applications such as image and video generation.
